## Components and Interfaces

### Flask Application (`app.py`)

Responsibilities:
- Read configuration from environment variables / `.env` file at startup
- Register REST API blueprints
- Serve `static/index.html` at `/`
- Start `Background_Watcher` daemon thread on startup
- Load `patch_timers.json` on startup (halt on parse error per Req 6.7)

```python
# Startup sequence (pseudocode)
config = load_config()          # env vars → config dict, warn on missing
validate_config(config)         # write warnings; halt only if stdout fails
load()                          # switch1_menu.load() — loads patch_timers.json
start_watcher()                 # switch1_menu.watcher() in daemon thread
app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=config["port"])
```

### REST API Layer (Flask routes in `app.py`)

All endpoints return `Content-Type: application/json`. Error responses always include `{"status": "error", "message": "..."}`.

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/` | Serve `static/index.html` |
| `GET` | `/api/ports` | All 114 ports + active patches with timer seconds |
| `POST` | `/api/patches` | Create a new patch |
| `DELETE` | `/api/patches/<patch_id>` | Remove a patch by tkey |
| `GET` | `/api/power` | Optical power readings for all 114 ports |

### Frontend (`static/index.html`)

Four logical views, each a `<section>` that is shown/hidden via CSS `display` toggling:

| View ID | Nav Label | Primary Content |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|
| `#view-dashboard` | Port Dashboard | 114-port grid + active patches table |
| `#view-create` | Create Patch | Form: portA, portB, duration, label |
| `#view-remove` | Remove Patch | List of active patches + confirm button |
| `#view-power` | Power Monitor | 114-port power grid + refresh button |

**JS module boundaries (IIFE pattern, no bundler):**

```
App (global state)
├── Router        — showView(viewId), highlights nav link
├── Api           — fetch wrappers (GET, POST, DELETE) returning Promises
├── Dashboard     — renderPortGrid(), renderPatchTable(), handleStaleData()
├── TimerManager  — syncTimers(patches), tick(), formatCountdown(secs)
├── CreatePatch   — validateForm(), submitPatch()
├── RemovePatch   — renderList(), confirmRemove(patchId)
├── PowerMonitor  — renderPowerGrid(), refresh()
└── Notifications — show(msg, level), clear()
```

